# Golf Tempo App – Project Structure Guide

This project is a Flutter app scaffolded with `flutter create`. Use this guide to quickly locate entry points, configuration, and where to add new features.

## Entry points and core files
- App entry: [lib/main.dart](mdc:lib/main.dart)
- Package config: [pubspec.yaml](mdc:pubspec.yaml)
- Lints/analysis: [analysis_options.yaml](mdc:analysis_options.yaml)
- Tests: [test/](mdc:test)

## Platforms
- iOS plist: [ios/Runner/Info.plist](mdc:ios/Runner/Info.plist)
- Android manifest: [android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml](mdc:android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml)
- Web: [web/](mdc:web)
- macOS: [macos/](mdc:macos)
- Windows: [windows/](mdc:windows)
- Linux: [linux/](mdc:linux)

## App organization (planned)
- UI/screens: `lib/ui/` (e.g., `lib/ui/home_screen.dart`)
- State management: `lib/state/` (e.g., Riverpod providers)
- Audio engine: `lib/audio/` (e.g., `lib/audio/audio_engine.dart`)
- Ads: `lib/ads/` (e.g., Banner widget + init)
- Theme: `lib/theme/`
- Utils: `lib/utils/`

## Assets (planned)
- Audio: `assets/audio/` (3 short WAV beeps: low/mid/high)
- Icons/images: `assets/images/`

Remember to register assets in [pubspec.yaml](mdc:pubspec.yaml) under `flutter:` → `assets:` when they are added.

## Run and build
- Analyze: `flutter analyze`
- Test: `flutter test`
- Run iOS simulator: `flutter run -d ios`
- Run Android emulator: `flutter run -d android`

## Notes
- Keep UI simple and accessible; banner ad sits at the bottom within a SafeArea.
- Avoid timers for audio timing; rely on the audio engine sequence (see Audio Engine rule).
